Prompt 1
Historical Theme: Art as divine power
Historical Period: Ancient Egypt
Artwork Used as Inspiration: Khafre with the Falcon God Horus
Visual Prompt:
Create a sculpture from Ancient Egypt showing a pharaoh sitting on a throne. The figure should look very straight, stiff, and balanced, with strong lines to show power and stability. The pharaoh should have an ideal body with no emotion on his face. Behind his head, include a falcon to represent a god protecting him. The sculpture should look large and important, making the pharaoh seem powerful.

The reason this artwork was made is to show that the pharaoh had divine power and was connected to the gods. In Ancient Egypt, art was not meant to look realistic but to show power, religion, and the idea that the ruler would live forever. This reflects how important religion and leadership were in their society.
